
quotes = ["To be creative means to be in love with life. You can be creative only if you love life enough that you want to enhance its beauty, you want to bring a little more music to it, a little more poetry to it, a little more dance to it.","The secret to creativity is knowing how to hide your sources.","If at first, the idea is not absurd, then there is no hope for it.","Imagination is everything. It is the preview of life’s coming attractions.","Logic will get you from A to B. Imagination will take you everywhere.","You can never solve a problem on the level on which it was created.","Information is not knowledge. The only source of knowledge is experience.","Creativity is contagious, pass it on.","Imagination is more important than knowledge.","A person who never made a mistake never tried anything new.","We cannot solve our problems with the same thinking we used when we created them.","Look deep into nature, and then you will understand everything better.","Learn from yesterday, live for today, hope for tomorrow. The important thing is to not stop questioning.","Creativity is just connecting things.","If you want to live your life in a creative way, as an artist, you have to not look back too much.","Be a yardstick of quality. Some people aren’t used to an environment where excellence is expected.","You can’t connect the dots looking forward; you can only connect them looking backwards.","The way to ratchet up our species is to get better things to more people  – products with spirit and creativity.","Your time is limited, so don’t waste it living someone else’s life.","Stay hungry, stay foolish.","It’s really hard to design products by focus groups. A lot of times, people don’t know what they want until you show it to them.","It’s more fun to be a pirate than to join the Navy.","Being the richest man in the cemetery doesn’t matter to me … Going to bed at night saying we’ve done something wonderful … that’s what matters to me.","Have the courage to follow your heart and intuition.","I want to put a ding in the universe.","Quality is more important than quantity. One home run is much better than two doubles.","Let’s go invent tomorrow rather than worrying about what happened yesterday.","Innovation is saying no to a thousand things.","I’m convinced that about half of what separates successful entrepreneurs from the non-successful ones is pure perseverance.","Don’t let the noise of other’s opinions drown out your own inner voice.","If today were the last of your life, would you do what you were going to do today?","It takes a lot of hard work to make something simple, to truly understand the underlying challenges and come up with elegant solutions.","It’s not just what it looks like and feels like. Design is how it works.","To design something really well, you have to get it. You have to really grok what it’s all about.","Invest time in yourself to have great experiences that are going to enrich you.","The most important thing is a person. A person who incites and feeds your curiosity; and machines cannot do that in the same way that people can.","Don’t think. Thinking is the enemy of creativity. You can’t try to do things. You simply must do things.","Creativity has got to start with humanity and when you’re a human being, you feel, you suffer.","The worst enemy to creativity is self-doubt.","Creativity makes life more fun and more interesting.","The comfort zone is the great enemy to creativity.","Creativity requires the courage to let go of certainties.","The chief enemy of creativity is good sense.","There is a fountain of youth: it is your mind, your talents, the creativity you bring to your life.","An essential aspect of creativity is not being afraid to fail.","Anxiety is part of creativity, the need to get something out.","Creativity is not the finding of a thing, but the making something out of it after it is found.","Anxiety is the handmaiden of creativity.","Creativity makes a leap, then looks to see where it is.","Normal means lack of imagination, lack of creativity.","This simple process of focusing on things that are normally taken for granted is a powerful source of creativity.","Enthusiasm is excitement with inspiration, motivation, and a pinch of creativity.","Creativity is breaking out of established patterns to look at things in a different way.","If you go with your instincts and keep your humor, creativity follows. With luck, success comes, too.","Creativity comes from a conflict of ideas.","Let us be about setting high standards for life, love, creativity, and wisdom.","Making the simple, awesomely simple, that’s creativity.","Creativity is a great motivator because it makes people interested in what they are doing.","When we are angry or depressed in our creativity, we have misplaced our power.","Creativity is a natural extension of our enthusiasm.","Creativity is the greatest expression of liberty.","Creativity is the ability to introduce order into the randomness of nature.","Creativity takes courage.","It was anger more than anything else that had set me off, roused me into productivity and creativity.","Creativity means to push open the heavy, groaning doorway to life.","Any activity becomes creative when the doer cares about doing it right, or better.","Energy is the key to creativity. Energy is the key to life.","Create whatever causes a revolution in your heart.","Creativity is the sudden cessation of stupidity.","People have a God-given right to use their creativity to produce things that improve our lives.","Creativity is what helps me escape a lot of my inner demons.","I go wherever my creativity takes me.","Clean out a corner of your mind and creativity will instantly fill it.","I try to manage my day by my circadian rhythms because the creativity is such an elusive thing.","The artistry and the creativity in a story are better than any drugs.","Creativity comes from looking for the unexpected and stepping outside your own experience.","Originality is the essence of true scholarship. Creativity is the soul of the true scholar.","Punishing honest mistakes stifles creativity.","To be creative means to be in love with life.","The refusal to be creative is self-will and is counter to our true nature.","Can’t kills creativity!","Creativity itself doesn’t care at all about results – the only thing it craves is the process.","Controversy is part of the nature of art and creativity.","The heart and soul of the company is creativity and innovation.","You can’t use up creativity. The more you use, the more you have.","Politics is the art of the possible; creativity is the art of the impossible.","We have the capacity for infinite creativity.","Creativity is piercing the mundane to find the marvelous.","Creativity comes from trust. Trust your instincts. And never hope more than you work.","I’ve found constancy and balance between creativity and normality.","It is better to fail in originality, than to succeed in imitation.","Creativity can be described as letting go of certainties.","A creative life is an amplified life.","I don’t know what I think until I write about it.","Creativity is thinking up new things. Innovation is doing new things.","Creativity is the natural order of life.","Creativity is allowing yourself to make mistakes. Art is knowing which ones to keep.","Without freedom, there is no creation.","Creative living is where Big Magic will always abide.","Every day is an opportunity to be creative.", "We are truly grateful for being a part of this journey!", "What would Jeevus do?", "There is nothing on this fortune cookie.", "Try again!", "What would Jeeves do?", "Let your developers update your system, oops gotta go! - Jeeves"]

  
  